State.Description: Dugongs and Manatees are aquatic peacefull herbivorous mammals, that inhabit lakes, estuaries and coastal marine waters. Three varieties exist in Skyrim, the small Manatee, the larger Dugong and the giant Sea Cow. All the 3 are massively hunted by nords for their meat, oil and fat.
State.Name: Dugongs and Manatees - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: One of the most impressive creations of the Dwemer are the Power Armors. When the Dwemer disappeared, they left behind all their arsenal, including their armored suits, over time, the Dwemer prodigious technological AI managed to hack and gain control over some of these extremely complex creations, re-engineering them into functional Automatons.
State.Name: Controlled Dwarven Power Suits - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''dwemer'')

State.Author: Mihail and SoN6of6TrediS
State.Description: Hungers are fierce lesser daedras, with a gaunt demonic appearance. They're consumed by constant and painfull hunger, and it's the agony of constant starving what makes them ruthless and unpredictable predators. Their inverted variant is known as Spitter, creatures that constantly need to spit out the fluids that over-satiate them.
State.Name: Hungers- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Iron Golems are magical powerfull constructs created by those practiced in the arcane arts. These bulky beings are fashioned from iron to resemble a giant human form, then animated and set to particular tasks. Defeating one is a feat well worth praise, for this rusty iron titans are formidable opponents.
State.Name: Iron Golem -Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Few things are more pitiful than the transformation of a soul into an insane wraith. Among these, there are those who have plunged into a deep mental abyss of sadness and despair, becoming what many know as Mourning Souls, the personification of desolation.
State.Name: Mourning Souls- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Soul Trees are created when a large number of persons are soul trapped together by a Daedra or necromancer. They form a grotesque whispering flesh effigee on Soul Cairn, not able to move or cry for help, and condemned to serve as soul essence for magic and enchantments for all the eternity.
State.Name: Soul Trees- Interesting Soul Cairn (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Men that die on battlefields usually can't peacefully accept their fate and will remain haunting the battlefields as ghosts. But when powerfull necromancers see this as an opportunity things can turn really dangerous, when these powerfull mages use dark magic to turn the enraged soldier ghosts into war revenants to serve them as obedient golens.
State.Name: War Revenants- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Tales mention water hags masquerading as lost old women to lure travelers back to the rickety shackes they build in the wetlands. Their wrinkled, wart-covered bodies stand neary two yards tall and stink of muck and fish. Bony growths two spans long stick out from their backs, with hair like a tangle of seaweed and claws.
State.Name: Water Hags- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Curious birds with exuberant black plumage, crows are docile and fearless animals, enjoying living close to human civilizations for their own benefit, feeding on leftovers left by their inhabitants.
State.Name: Crows- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwarven Colossus are one of the magnum opus amongst Animunculi,  they are massive, with incredible endurance and fire power. They possess specialized weapons on their arms, a large dual-blade gauntlet on the right and a hammer piston that creates fire pulses on the left. They are also able to breath extremely destructive fire.
State.Name: Dwarven Colossus - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Created to be the pawns on the front line of the Dwemer army, Dwarven Defenders are articulated automatons designed to emulate the combat skills of their creators in wars and conflicts. Wielding light dwarven shields, and sledgehammers, and firing blasts of electricity through their central core, these machine armies are a force to be feared.
State.Name: Dwarven Defenders- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dwemers used to adapt some of their war automatons to perform trivial functions. Some of them were Dwarven Ballistas who had their bolt launching platform removed, and in its place were installed sets of spinning blades typically used as traps in dwemer ruins. These modified automatons were used for harvesting and became known as Dwarven Threshers.
State.Name: Dwarven Threshers- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The pesky Foglings are small, self-mutilating goblin-like lesser vampires who live in a permanent semi-ethereal state due to their low intelligence and inability to master the powers and effects of vampirism. They live in constant agony as they insist on coming out of their hiding places during the day, thus burning their skins painfully.
State.Name: Foglings- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Materialized from obscure childhood fears, what could be more frightening than a profound trauma turned into a solid, horrifying form of flesh and blood, which returns from the past forgotten in time, to torment those who try to forget it at all costs?
State.Name: Grey Children- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

Original.Name: Hungers - Optimized textures SE-AE by Xtudo - 2K version-84435-1-1675774782.7z

State.Author: Xtudo
State.Description: My optimized textures for the terrifying Hungers - Mihail Monsters and Animals mod. 4K-2K-1K. No ESP.
State.Name: Hungers - My optimized textures SE-AE

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The ancient race of the Titans are powerful primeval giant sentient beings, with brutal elemental magic powers. In 4th Era only a handful of them are still alive. The Ice Titans are one of them, with a blue skinned huge body with a deformed head on top of it,  long snow covered hair,  and using rudimentary armors made of fur, bones and ship junk.
State.Name: Ice Titans- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

Original.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt (SE) 1.4.1 version-27520-1-4-1-1651832785.rar

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Old Gods of the Hunt, also known as Ancient Leshens, are powerfull ancient creatures from a previous Wild Hunt, that still roams through Tamriel in very small numbers. Ferocious and stunning powerfull, this wild hunt beasts are related to Hircine, and worshiped since the beginning by the Forsworn and the Bosmer as one of their Old Gods.
State.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: These ferocious men-bull descendants of Morihaus are said to have symbolized the Alessian Empire during the 1st Era, but later became commonly seen as dangerous beasts by other races. The variant that inhabits Skyrim is among those closest to the original glory and power of its race, unlike other more ferocious variants that live across Tamriel.
State.Name: Minotaurs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Shambles are animated constructs of bones from the Shivering Isles, arranged in an unusual way and tied together using thongs of frayed leather, with rusted iron medallions that firmly attach these thongs to the dry, brittle bones. Due to their fragile and illogical construction, it is common for Shambles to lose limbs, and even their heads.
State.Name: Shambles- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''shivering isles'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Encounters with Zombies and Wights, while always unpleasant, are relatively common for an adventurer exploring Skyrim, but tales of an encounter with a reanimated ancient Snow Elf is something that strays into the realm of myth, and will make many roll their eyes, as if they were listening to just another fairy tale, told to frighten children.
State.Name: Undead Snow Elves- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''falmer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Vigilants are peculiar floating blue daedra with eight large tentacles ending in triangular fins, connected to a small round body with one large central eye on each side and appearance similar to the eyes of octopuses. They also have an antenna that produces light in its end, similar to that used by some benthic fish, with unknown use.
State.Name: Vigilants- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''watcher'')
